<p>A Labs member asked for a way to open a folder from anywhere on his Mac. Here’s a Keyboard Maestro macro that uses the URL call action to solve the problem. This is a handy technique that can be deployed in several ways on your Mac. Here I show a use case involving the Notes field from an OmniFocus action. … This is a post for the MacSparky Labs Pathfinder and Insider members. <a href="https://www.macsparky.com/join/">Care to join?</a> If you’re already a member,<a href="https://www.macsparky.com/?memberful_endpoint=auth"> you can log in here.</a></p>
